parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle, accompanied by brake failure, can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes are inoperative
the vehicle fails to stop
the RPM runs high even after shifting into park
the pre-collision system feature does not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system, accompanied by warning lights, can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities if the driver is not aware of the issue or fails to take immediate action.
symptoms: The brake failure warning lights come on
the brakes are inoperative
the vehicle fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BOS can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities if the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down in emergency situations.
symptoms: The BOS fails to prevent the collision or even warn of the impending collision
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become hard to maneuver, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and put other road users at risk.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel requires excessive force to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel does not respond properly to input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Diagnosis and Repair by Dealership
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealership to properly diagnose and address the issue can lead to prolonged exposure to the safety risks associated with the malfunctioning power steering system.
symptoms: The dealership is unable to confirm or address the issue despite multiple inspections
the issue persists or worsens over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation of the interior door beam can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially leading to reduced safety in the event of a side-impact accident, which could result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The interior door beam on the driver's side has a dent-like deformation
the stainless steel beam has sucked in
and there is no clear explanation for the cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clogging of the HVAC evaporator drain hose can cause water to overflow into the cabin, resulting in water damage, mold, and mildew on the carpet and pad. This can lead to costly repairs and create an unhealthy environment for occupants.
symptoms: Water accumulation on the driver-side floor
water overflow when using the AC or defroster
mold and mildew growth on the carpet and pad.
